         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">5/9/81. ¶  ¶ I have to thank you, dear Mr Dyer, for the photograms of Cycadeae, received from you. It needs not my assurance, that I will gladly aid you in any monographic work on that order; but it s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.09.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 317.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/9/81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you, dear Mr Dyer, for the photograms of Cycadeae, received from you. It needs not my assurance, that I will gladly aid you in any monographic work on that order; but it so happened, that my interest in the Cycads awoke anew, when I elaborated the description of Zamia Moorei,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B81.03.01, p. 84, as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Macrozamia moorei.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and I put myself then in communication with several correspondents in regions, where <name key="Cycadeae%20">Cycadeae </name>grow, to obtain additional material and fuller notes on several species<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See, for example, F Kempe to M, 9 July 1881, and P O'Shanesy to M, 17 August 1881.</p>
               </note> I presume, there is no great hurry about this, especially as you must be very busy in spare hours to finish the 4th vol of the flora Capensis.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thiselton-Dyer's continuation of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora capensis </seg>commenced by Harvey and Sonder was long delayed. Vols. 6 and 7 appeared in 1896-7 and 1897-1900 respectively, but the two sections of vol. 4 were not published until 1909 and 1904 (TL2).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Meanwhile palaeontologic research goes also on, so that you can do justice to the <name key="Cycadeae%20">Cycadeae </name>also of former ages</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The name Peroffskian[a]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <name key="Macrozamia%20peroffskiana">Macrozamia peroffskiana</name>.</p>
               </note> among these noble plants, uncalled for as it was,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For M’s earlier comments on the inappropriateness of the name see M to G. Bentham 26 September 1873, in this edition as 73-09-26a.</p>
               </note> ought to be banished after the imperatricidal horrors of St Petersburg.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tsar Alexander II of Russia was assassinated on 13 March (1 March O.S.) 1881. One of those alleged to be involved was ‘the woman Perowsky’ (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">The Times</seg>, 26 March 1881, p. 7).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks for the fragments of Euc. stricta.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Thiselton Dyer, 7 May 1881.</p>
               </note> I am now at last free from the work of the international Exhibition;<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1.</p>
               </note> so I can resume the writing of the text for the Eucalyptography<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably for Decade 8 (B82.13.17). <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. stricta</seg> appeared in Decade 10 (B84.11.02).</p>
               </note> &amp; for some other works under progress.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">We look forward with great interest to your report on the Bordeaux Congress, concerning the Phylloxera Vastatrix.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thiselton-Dyer (1882). In his Introduction, dated 5 September 1882, Thiselton Dyer wrote: </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.5299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust the unavoidable delay on my part, from the pressure of multifarious official duties, in submitting this report, will not have entailed any inconvenience. The postponement has, at any rate, afforded me the opportunity of obtaining authentic information, which I trust will be found to be not without value. (¶22, p. 9).</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thiselton-Dyer was paid an honorarium of 100 guineas (£105), receipt of which he acknowledged in a letter of 26 October 1882 (copy at RBG Kew, Archives. Misc. Reports 1.52. Bordeaux Congress [1881], f. 86). For the background to Thiselton-Dyer’s appointment, see M to J. Hooker, 23 July 1881 and notes thereto.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will try to procure for you a tall stem of <name key="Cycas%20media">Cycas media</name>, but this cannot be done for a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">few</hi>
               </seg> £.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari was quite wrong in reducing <name key="Cycas%20papuana">Cycas papuana</name> as he acknowledged subsequently<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90), vol. 1, p. 178. Beccari's retraction has not been found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cycadeae%20">Cycadeae </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cycas%20media">Cycas media</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cycas%20papuana">Cycas papuana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20stricta">Eucalyptus stricta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Macrozamia%20peroffskiana">Macrozamia peroffskiana</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
